abstract: >-
  A practitioner's reference for shipping enterprise AI agents in production.
  Three Parts — Foundations (the 10-tier agent stack, the 7 LangGraph
  topologies, the 6 recipe families at intro depth, the 3 identity problems,
  the named-incident anchors, the evidence-class taxonomy); Patterns (the
  framework landscape at procurement-grade depth, the topologies at deployment
  depth, the recipes with audit-evidence patterns and failure-mode runbooks
  and 30/60/90 postures, the Identity / Agent AuthZ section at full depth, the
  ICP segment variants, the governance categories with cross-tenant five-
  surface enumeration, the deployment shapes, the hyperscaler Rosetta Stone +
  WAF-pillar cross-walk, the exit-portability skeleton); Production (the 10-
  axis deployment-shape matrix, the Cross-Tenant Isolation section, the
  Integration Cookbook, the Audit-Evidence Cookbook, the per-regime
  regulatory depth chapters, the 14 governance failure modes at expert depth,
  the recipe-by-recipe Production deep-dives, the operational-lifecycle role-
  play, the capstone). LangGraph-anchored (eighteen of eighteen named
  customer-disclosed enterprise deployments in the public corpus surveyed are
  LangGraph) while surveying the broader landscape across ~27 frameworks
  including CrewAI, AutoGen / AG2, Microsoft Agent Framework, OpenAI Agents
  SDK, LlamaIndex Workflows, Semantic Kernel, AWS Bedrock AgentCore, Azure AI
  Foundry, GCP Vertex Agent Engine, NVIDIA AI-Q, IBM watsonx Orchestrate,
  Salesforce Agentforce. Audience: anyone shipping enterprise AI agents —
  Sales Engineers, Solution Consultants, Product Managers, Forward Deployed
  Engineers, developers, Enterprise Architects, CISOs. Citation discipline:
  every factual claim carries one of ten evidence-class tags.
